          "state_reason": "completed",
          "title": "rpcbind required for remote connections?",
          "body": "# Issue Template\r\n\r\n## Context\r\n\r\nUnable to connect to the daemon, unless daemon is binded to network card ip address. rpcallow does not work.\r\n\r\n## Prerequisites\r\n\r\n5.0.0 develop\r\nUbuntu 18.04\r\n\r\n## User Story:\r\n\r\n  **MAYBE**: [ ] bug report ðŸ˜„ \r\n\r\nThe daemons looks like its bound to 0.0.0.0 which should allow access across all network devices, right? (Assuming remote device IP address is allowed in config)\r\n```\r\ntcp        0      0 0.0.0.0:15556      0.0.0.0:*               LISTEN      26544/verged\r\ntcp        0      0 0.0.0.0:15559           0.0.0.0:*               LISTEN      26544/verged\r\ntcp6       0      0 :::15559                :::*                    LISTEN      26544/verged\r\n```\r\nThis works on other daemons at least. However i was not able to communicate with the new verge daemon using this method, however by starting the daemon with a specified `--rpcbind=192.168.1.50` - i can access the daemon remotely with a computer on the same network:\r\n```\r\ntcp        0      192.168.1.50:15556      0.0.0.0:*               LISTEN      30664/verged\r\ntcp        0      0 0.0.0.0:15559           0.0.0.0:*               LISTEN      30664/verged\r\ntcp6       0      0 :::15559                :::*                    LISTEN      30664/verged\r\n```\r\n\r\nNot really a problem since it can be binded to a specific IP, and heck its even safer, but i though is should put some light on this.",
