          "title": "Unhandled connection error: connection refused",
          "body": "I'm trying to set up Joinmarket and when running `python joinmarket-qt.py`, I'm experiencing the same issue as described here:  https://github.com/JoinMarket-Org/joinmarket-clientserver/issues/374 but unfortunately, nothing from that thread helped.\r\n\r\nI run Bitcoin Core on a Raspberry Pi and Joinmarket on a Mac (through Terminal). \r\n\r\nThe relevant parts of the bitcoin.conf file (on the Raspberry Pi) look like this: \r\n\r\n> daemon=1\r\n>txindex=1\r\n>server=1\r\n>rpcuser= *X*\r\n>rpcpassword=*Y*\r\n>zmqpubrawblock=tcp://127.0.0.1:28332\r\n>zmqpubrawtx=tcp://127.0.0.1:28333\r\n>rpcport=8332\r\n>\r\n> \\# Joinmarket\r\n>walletnotify=curl -sI --connect-timeout 1 http://localhost:62602/walletnotify?%s\r\n>alertnotify=curl -sI --connect-timeout 1 http://localhost:62602/alertnotify?%s\r\n\r\n\r\nThe joinmarket.cfg (on my local machine) looks like this: \r\n\r\n> [BLOCKCHAIN]\r\n>blockchain_source = bitcoin-rpc\r\n>network = mainnet\r\n>rpc_host = localhost\r\n>rpc_port = 8332\r\n>rpc_user = *X*\r\n>rpc_password = *Y*\r\n>rpc_wallet_file =\r\n\r\nThe user/password are identical in both .conf files. I also tried to put the local IP of my Pi in the `localhost` line but no avail. \r\nCurl is installed. Bitcoin Core is running and is fully synced.  \r\n\r\nAny other ideas what might be wrong?",
